If there ever will be a PC port, which I've honestly kinda given up on, I'm gonna put in another 150+ hours and get the plat again. Even if that means doing chalice dungeons again. It would be worth it.

So basically... While Elden Ring is an incredible game, and I've loved exploring the Lands Between, I do believe Bloodborne is still my favorite. 10/10, would buy a PS4 just for it again in a heartbeat.

The only things that could make the game flawless imo are:
Refilling blood vials when returning to your world after co-op, and better performance.
A respec system would be nice but it's not the end of the world to me.

The first playthrough is breath-taking, and all the ones that follow are also fun. It's just... it's just so good lmao. It scratches an itch that the other games just don't, even though they're so amazing.

In other FromSoft games I've struggled to finish two playthroughs, even though I love them so much. But Bloodborne? On my first character I'm in NG+2, and I have about four other characters that I've played a lot with. One of them is in NG+. For me, that's a *lot*.
Gehrman, Lady Maria, Ludwig... Those three alone already make the game perfection in my eyes. I adore them. And there's so many other fights that are really fun, even several playthroughs later.
Sometimes when I'm in a bad mood I just boot the game to sit in the Hunter's Dream. It's my home. There's something so incredibly calming to it that I simply don't feel with the others.
Every few months I get that pull to return to Yharnam. Bloodborne is such a perfectly crafted experience. The atmosphere is unmatched. Despite the garbage performance I still love it to bits.

This is... so hard. Bloodborne has reigned as my favorite game of all time for two years. Elden Ring takes everything good from Demon's Souls to Sekiro and puts it into a beautiful world. It's their most polished game.

I could honestly gush about this game all day but long story short. FFXIV is one of the best things to have happened to me and I’m not exaggerating. So shoutout to this gif for literally living in my head rent-free and bugging me long enough until I tried it. https://t.co/25LHXCEhGa

You have to WORK to get there, and then it’s just you, Alphi, and Tataru, entering a city whose gates have been closed for so long. You are not welcome by the people. And then the fucking music? I was in love immediately. And it just Kept Getting Better.
The ending of ARR made me go Oh Shit maybe this game is different and worth seeing to the end. But the very second I stepped into Ishgard is when I truly fell in love with the game.
I didn’t intend to make an embarrassingly long thread but you know what we’re already here so might as well continue! I’m cringe but I am free.

Idk how others can get through the MSQ so fast and not be phased. I’m not even a slow reader, but I guess I did take it slower overall to really be able to take it all in rather than just read it and see what sticks.

To think that I did all of Heavensward, Stormblood, and most of Shadowbringers in November without skipping anything and only occasionally doing not-MSQ is uhhhhh… how. Don’t do that. Don’t be me. I did base SHB in four days because I legit barely slept.

I ended my free trial on the 7th of November early because a friend wanted to play together and I wanted to be able to invite them. I was in early Heavensward at that point I believe, playing for ~2 weeks.

I did ARR including the patch quests in ~10 days once I started playing seriously. And everything followed so flipping fast. I was on crack, inhaling the game an unhealthy amount 🤡 (I’m talking like 15+ hours a day every day, ESPECIALLY in Shadowbringers, almost only doing MSQ).

Then after my birthday, I decided to just go fucking ham. I don’t remember what changed. I think I just wanted to find out what the story is all about—and maybe part of me wanted to see if I could catch up in time for Endwalker. It wasn’t my only motivation, but def one of them.

Idk how people play without one, I legit can’t function without my MMO mouse. It definitely took me ~60 hours to get fully used to it, since it was all new to me, but it was worth it. Don’t think I would’ve stuck around if I hadn’t gotten one I’ll be real.

Then I got kinda busy but I thought well I’ll probably stick around for a bit so I should get an MMO mouse, because I could Not see myself using keybinds on my keyboard. It was my birthday gift to myself, and it was one of the best god damn things I did last year.

I honestly just played it to kill time since I had nothing better to do. Played it extremely casually, only every other day or so for maybe an hour, made very little progress. But it had already wormed its way into my heart; I just hadn’t noticed it yet.

I slowly made my way through the quests, reading everything cause I knew if I was giving this game a shot the least I could do was give it a fair one. You only get one first playthrough, and I didn’t want to regret it later on in case I did stick around (BLESS).

I got in, felt overwhelmed, didn’t really enjoy it. But it had charm. Some of the writing was incredibly dated and I wasn’t invested at all (mind you, I was still only in Gridania). But something made me come back the next day, just for an hour or so.

Then when I got burnt out with G/enshin I decided to just say fuck it, it’s free, I’ve heard the meme for ages. Most definitely not gonna stick around. I was going in expecting to drop it. I was feeling incredibly down that day so I had nothing left to lose anyways.
